SIMPLE: titulary
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Titulary
<hw>Tit"u*la*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Titularies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>titulaire</ets>.]</ety> <def>A person invested with a title, in
virtue of which he holds an office or benefice, whether he performs the
duties of it or not.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Titulary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Titulary
<hw>Tit"u*la*ry</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Consisting in a
title; titular.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to a title.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tituled</ent>⟦br⟧
